JuniIpsecIdentityType.name: JuniIpsecIdentityType
JuniIpsecIdentityType.description: The type of IPsec Phase-1 identity. The Phase-1 identity may be identified by one of the ID types defined in IPSEC DOI.

JuniIpsecTransformType.name: JuniIpsecTransformType
JuniIpsecTransformType.description: The transform algorithm for the IPsec tunnel.

JuniIpsecPfsGroup.name: JuniIpsecPfsGroup
JuniIpsecPfsGroup.description: The perfect forward secrecy group. Group1 - 768-bit DH prime modulus group. Group2 - 1024-bit DH prime modulus group. Group5 - 1536-bit DH prime modulus group.

Spi.name: Spi
Spi.description: The type of the SPI associated with IPsec Phase-2 security associations.

juniIpsecTunnelNextIfIndex.name: juniIpsecTunnelNextIfIndex
juniIpsecTunnelNextIfIndex.description: Coordinate ifIndex value allocation for entries in the juniIpsecTunnelIfTable. A GET of this object returns the next available ifIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated interface table; or zero, if no valid ifIndex value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

juniIpsecTunnelInterfaceTable.name: juniIpsecTunnelInterfaceTable
juniIpsecTunnelInterfaceTable.description: This table contains entries of IPsec Tunnel interfaces.

juniIpsecTunnelInterfaceEntry.name: juniIpsecTunnelInterfaceEntry
juniIpsecTunnelInterfaceEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of a single IPsec Tunnel interface. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries for be created/deleted in ifTable/ifXTable/juniIfTable.

juniIpsecTunnelIfIndex.name: juniIpsecTunnelIfIndex
juniIpsecTunnelIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the IPsec tunnel interface. When creating entries in this table, suitable values for this object are determined by reading juniIpsecTunnelNextIfIndex.

juniIpsecTunnelName.name: juniIpsecTunnelName
juniIpsecTunnelName.description: The administratively assigned name for this IPsec Tunnel interface. Before configuring other tunnel attributes, IPsec tunnel has to be created with minimum attributes (tunnel name and rowStatus).

juniIpsecTunnelType.name: juniIpsecTunnelType
juniIpsecTunnelType.description: The configured mode for this IPsec Tunnel interface.

juniIpsecTunnelTransportVirtualRouter.name: juniIpsecTunnelTransportVirtualRouter
juniIpsecTunnelTransportVirtualRouter.description: The transport virtual router associated with this IPsec tunnel interface. This object need not be set when creating row entries. Note that the default when this object is not specified is the router associated with the agent acting on the management request.

juniIpsecTunnelTransformSet.name: juniIpsecTunnelTransformSet
juniIpsecTunnelTransformSet.description: The transform set. It refers to a transform set that is defined in the transform set table.

juniIpsecTunnelSrcType.name: juniIpsecTunnelSrcType
juniIpsecTunnelSrcType.description: The tunnel source type. The tunnel source may be identified by: 1. an IP(V4) address, or 2. a fully qualified domain name string, or 3. a user fully qualified domain name string.

juniIpsecTunnelDstType.name: juniIpsecTunnelDstType
juniIpsecTunnelDstType.description: The tunnel destination type. The tunnel destination may be identified by: 1. an IP(V4) address, or 2. a fully qualified domain name string, or 3. a user fully qualified domain name string.

juniIpsecTunnelBackupDstType.name: juniIpsecTunnelBackupDstType
juniIpsecTunnelBackupDstType.description: The tunnel backup destination type. The tunnel backup destination type has to be the same as the tunnel destination type The tunnel destination may be identified by: 1. an IP(V4) address, or 2. a fully qualified domain name string, 3. a user fully qualified domain name string.

juniIpsecTunnelBackupDstAddr.name: juniIpsecTunnelBackupDstAddr
juniIpsecTunnelBackupDstAddr.description: The tunnel backup destination IP(V4) address.

juniIpsecTunnelLocalIdType.name: juniIpsecTunnelLocalIdType
juniIpsecTunnelLocalIdType.description: The tunnel phase-2 local identity type. The tunnel local identity type may be identified by: 1. an IP address, or 2. an IP address subnet, or 3. an IP address range.

juniIpsecTunnelLocalIdAddr1.name: juniIpsecTunnelLocalIdAddr1
juniIpsecTunnelLocalIdAddr1.description: The tunnel local phase-2 identity IP address 1.

juniIpsecTunnelLocalIdAddr2.name: juniIpsecTunnelLocalIdAddr2
juniIpsecTunnelLocalIdAddr2.description: The tunnel local phase-2 identity IP address 2 in the case the identity type is an IP address range. The tunnel local phase-2 identity netmask in the case the identity type is an IP address subnet.

juniIpsecTunnelRemoteIdType.name: juniIpsecTunnelRemoteIdType
juniIpsecTunnelRemoteIdType.description: The tunnel phase-2 remote identity type. The tunnel remote identity type may be identified by: 1. an IP address, or 2. an IP address subnet, or 3. an IP address range.

juniIpsecTunnelRemoteIdAddr1.name: juniIpsecTunnelRemoteIdAddr1
juniIpsecTunnelRemoteIdAddr1.description: The tunnel remote phase-2 identity IP address 1.

juniIpsecTunnelRemoteIdAddr2.name: juniIpsecTunnelRemoteIdAddr2
juniIpsecTunnelRemoteIdAddr2.description: The tunnel remote phase-2 identity IP address 2 in the case the identity type is an IP address range. The tunnel remote phase-2 identity netmask in the case the identity type is an IP address subnet.

juniIpsecTunnelPfsGroup.name: juniIpsecTunnelPfsGroup
juniIpsecTunnelPfsGroup.description: The tunnel perfect forward secrecty group.

juniIpsecTunnelRowStatus.name: juniIpsecTunnelRowStatus
juniIpsecTunnelRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: juniIpsecTunnelIfRowStatus juniIpsecTunnelName In addition, when creating an entry the following condition must hold: A value for juniIpsecTunnelIfIndex must have been determined previously, typically by reading juniIpsecTunnelNextIfIndex. Once created, the following objects may not be modified: juniIpsecTunnelName juniIpsecTunnelVirtualRouter A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/juniIfTable is created/ destroyed as a result of creating/destroying an entry in this table.

juniIpsecTunnelStatTable.name: juniIpsecTunnelStatTable
juniIpsecTunnelStatTable.description: The IPsec tunnel interface statistics table. Describes the IPsec tunnel inbound/outbound statistics on IPsec de/encapsulation, de/encryption, and related error statistics.

juniIpsecTunnelStatEntry.name: juniIpsecTunnelStatEntry
juniIpsecTunnelStatEntry.description: Describes the ipsec traffic statistics of the ipsec tunnel interface.

juniIpsecTunnelStatIfIndex.name: juniIpsecTunnelStatIfIndex
